I lost my guise of the deciever to a bug, <br>
and Verant CS didn't want to reimburse it.<br>
<br>
Here's the basics of what happened.<br>
<br>
Chapter One, no GM.<br>
<br>
Me: I lost my guise<br>
Guide: How may I help you?<br>
Me: I lost my guise<br>
Guide: I'll escalate, a GM will get back to you.<br>
Me: [stays online for x hours, never get a response]<br>
<br>
Repeat chapter one 10 times or so.<br>
<br>
Chapter two, the allmighty GM.<br>
<br>
GM: Hi...<br>
Me: Wow! A GM at last!<br>
GM: Lost the guise, huh?<br>
Me: Aye.<br>
GM: It's not in my log that you have ever owned one.<br>
Me: What?<br>
GM: I checked the log for the last three weeks, it's not there.<br>
Me: It must have poofed earlier then that. I havn't played much this month, <br>
and since I didn't destroy it I don't know when it was destroyed.<br>
GM: Whatever.<br>
Me: I spent more then a week of these three weeks waiting for you <br>
to get online and respond to the petition I got escalated each day.<br>
GM: That's your problem, it's not out responsibility to keep logs. <br>
(Yes, the GM actually said this.)<br>
Me: I'll mail Verant CS then.<br>
GM: Don't bother, my rulings are final.<br>
Me: &quot;There's noone with that name online at this time&quot;. <br>
(I.e. the GM logged on me.)<br>
<br>
Chapter Three, mailing Verant<br>
<br>
Me: I lost my guise, lots of details, yada yada<br>
Verant: We checked the logs, no guise.<br>
Me: Have you checked older logs? Some time have passed now...<br>
Verant: We checked back to mars. No guise, I'm telling you.<br>
Me: It must be there. My oldest screenshot with the guise is from may. <br>
Please check that you looked for the right character, server, et cetera, <br>
and the PRE-nerf guise.<br>
Verant: We tripplechecked the oldest logs just for you, <br>
but you have never owned a pre nerf guise of the deciever.<br>
Me: (no reply) <br>
Verant: Hi! We have checked our logs, verified your guise and reimbursed it. <br>
Have a nice day!<br>
<br>
End<br>
<br>
<br>
/shrug<br>
